    },
    {
      "id": "00b107ab_699fbfd6",
      "file_path": "dmaap-sim/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/sim/provider/DmaapSimProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 61,
      "message": "actually, this depends on the application media type.  If it's application/json, then this is an array of strings (i.e., messages).\n\nHowever, I believe the cambria client publisher actually uses application/cambria, which is a more compressed form, in which case, it would have to be decoded from that instead.  In other words, I don't think any of the clients will be able to publish to this simulator. :-(  However, we can certainly use curl to post messages to it.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-15 16:07:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "aab1cddc_bde04040",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "8565248c_c98b3d5b",
      "file_path": "dmaap-sim/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/sim/provider/DmaapSimProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 110,
      "message": "remove the do-loop and replace with queue.await(timeout)\n\ncan choose to just return one message at a time, or could return up to the client-specified limit.  If choose to do the latter, then only await(timeout) for the first message, the others should simply use poll() until the message count limit is reached or poll() returns null",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-15 16:07:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
